.SH "EXIT STATUS"
0  Success
2  Invalid arguments
3  Invalid configuration
10 Ableton not connected
11 Remote Script not installed/detected
12 Timeout
13 Protocol mismatch
20 Execution failure
99 Internal error
.SH FILES
Default config file:

  ~/.config/ableton-cli/config.toml
.SH EXAMPLES
Check connectivity:

  ableton-cli ping

Get structured JSON for automation:

  ableton-cli --output json song info

Global options must come before subcommands:

  ableton-cli --output json doctor

Set tempo:

  ableton-cli transport tempo set 128

Create clip and add notes:

  ableton-cli clip create 0 0 --length 4
  ableton-cli clip notes add 0 0 --notes-json '[{"pitch":60,"start_time":0.0,"duration":0.5,"velocity":100,"mute":false}]'
  ableton-cli clip notes add 0 0 --notes-file ./notes.json
  ableton-cli clip notes get 0 0 --start-time 0.0 --end-time 4.0 --pitch 60

Scenes and mixer operations:

  ableton-cli scenes list
  ableton-cli scenes create --index 1
  ableton-cli scenes fire 1
  ableton-cli session stop-all-clips
  ableton-cli session snapshot
  ableton-cli track mute set 0 true
  ableton-cli track panning set 0 -- -0.25

Config and protocol override:

  ableton-cli config set protocol_version 2
  ableton-cli --protocol-version 2 ping

Browser/device operations:

  ableton-cli browser tree all
  ableton-cli browser items-at-path drums/Kits
  ableton-cli browser search drift --item-type loadable
  ableton-cli browser item query:Synths#Operator
  ableton-cli browser load 0 query:Synths#Operator
  ableton-cli browser load-drum-kit 0 rack:drums --kit-uri kit:acoustic
  ableton-cli batch run --steps-file ./steps.json
  ableton-cli batch run --steps-json '{"steps":[{"command":"song_info","args":{}}}'
  echo '{"steps":[{"command":"song_info","args":{}}]}' | ableton-cli batch run --steps-stdin
  ableton-cli wait-ready
  ableton-cli device parameter set 0 0 0 0.25
  ableton-cli synth find --type wavetable
  ableton-cli synth parameters list 0 0
  ableton-cli synth parameter set 0 0 0 0.5
  ableton-cli synth observe 0 0
  ableton-cli synth wavetable keys
  ableton-cli synth wavetable set 0 0 filter_cutoff 0.6
  ableton-cli synth wavetable observe 0 0
  ableton-cli synth drift keys
  ableton-cli synth drift set 0 0 drift_amount 0.4
  ableton-cli synth drift observe 0 0
  ableton-cli synth meld keys
  ableton-cli synth meld set 0 0 spread_amount 0.3
  ableton-cli synth meld observe 0 0
  ableton-cli effect find --type eq8
  ableton-cli effect parameters list 0 0
  ableton-cli effect parameter set 0 0 0 0.5
  ableton-cli effect parameter set 0 0 7 -- -2.0
  ableton-cli effect observe 0 0
  ableton-cli effect eq8 keys
  ableton-cli effect eq8 set 0 0 band1_freq 0.6
  ableton-cli effect eq8 observe 0 0
  ableton-cli effect limiter keys
  ableton-cli effect limiter set 0 0 ceiling 0.4
  ableton-cli effect limiter observe 0 0
  ableton-cli effect compressor keys
  ableton-cli effect compressor set 0 0 ratio 0.5
  ableton-cli effect compressor observe 0 0
  ableton-cli effect auto-filter keys
  ableton-cli effect auto-filter set 0 0 lfo_rate 0.25
  ableton-cli effect auto-filter observe 0 0
  ableton-cli effect reverb keys
  ableton-cli effect reverb set 0 0 size 0.55
  ableton-cli effect reverb observe 0 0
  ableton-cli effect utility keys
  ableton-cli effect utility set 0 0 width 0.75
  ableton-cli effect utility observe 0 0

After updating Remote Script files (install-remote-script), reload Ableton's Control Surface
selection (`None` then `AbletonCliRemote`) or restart Ableton Live.

To confirm the latest script is active, run:

  ableton-cli --output json ping

and check `result.remote_script_version` plus `result.supported_commands`.

When a positional numeric value starts with "-", insert `--` before the value:

  ableton-cli track panning set 0 -- -0.25
  ableton-cli effect parameter set 0 0 7 -- -2.0

Standard wrapper commands (`synth <type> ...`, `effect <type> ...`) are strict. If
you receive "Missing required standard ... keys", use generic indexed commands:

  ableton-cli --output json effect parameters list <track> <device>
  ableton-cli --output json effect parameter set <track> <device> <parameter> <value>
.SH "SEE ALSO"
ableton-cli --help
